<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n41066d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n41" href="#n41066d">N41 (VI.B.33)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n41all.htm#n41066d"> 66(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font face="wake">C</font> looks W</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Since the love of ruling from the love of self is entirely opposed to love to the Lord, therefore spirits who are in that love of ruling, turn the face away from the Lord, and therefore they <mark>look with the eyes to the west</mark> of the spiritual world, and thus because of the wrong conversion of their bodies, have the east behind them, the north at their right, and the south at their left. <small> Emanuel Swedenborg, <a name="ESAW" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ESAW"><cite title="source">Angelic Wisdom Concerning the Divine Love</cite></a> (ed. unknown) 144</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
